data.enText: used to show that sth is almost, but not completely, accurate or correct
The journey took approximately seven hours.
data.chText: 旅程大约花了七个小时。

ex.enText: She has around ten million US dollars in the bank.
ex.chText: 她在银行里存有大约一千万美元。

ex.enText: Janet left here around seven o'clock.
ex.chText: 珍妮特大约7点钟离开这里的。

synonyms.bx: 多用于非正式场合，常见于美国英语。也用作 around about。

ex.enText: They left the museum at about 10 o'clock.
ex.chText: 他们10点左右离开了博物馆。
他住的地方离这里5英里左右。

synonyms.bx: 表示实际数量可多可少或数值、尺寸等可大可小，也作 round about。

ex.enText: The plane will be taking off in approximately ten minutes.
He owes me approximately 400 US dollars.

synonyms.bx: 多用于书面语，强调接近精确数值、数量、时间等，误差较小。

ex.enText: The Antarctica is a continent centred roughly on the South Pole.
ex.chText: 南极洲是一片大致以南极为中心的大陆。

synonyms.bx: 指按粗略估计，不强调十分接近精确数值。

tr: (of quantities) imprecise but fairly close to correct
example: I've had about all I can stand
we meet about once a month
20 or so people were at the party

value.boxr_value: The adjective is pronounced /ə'prɒksɪmət/. The verb is pronounced /ə'prɒksɪmeɪt/. 形容词读作 /ə'prɒksɪmət/，动词读作 /ə'prɒksɪ- meɪt/。

example.ex: The approximate cost varies from around £150 to £250...
example.tran: 费用大概介于150至250英镑之间。

value.def: An approximate number, time, or position is close to the correct number, time, or position, but is not exact.

example.ex: Approximately $150 million is to be spent on improvements.
example.tran: 大约1.5亿美元将用于作出改善。

example.ex: They did not have even an approximate idea what the Germans really wanted.
example.tran: 他们完全不清楚德国人真正想要什么。

value.def: An idea or description that is approximate is not intended to be precise or accurate, but to give some indication of what something is like.

example.ex: Something approximating to a fair outcome will be ensured...
example.tran: 保证会有大致公正的结果。

example.ex: By about 6 weeks of age, most babies begin to show something approximating a day/night sleeping pattern.
example.tran: 到6个星期大时，大多数婴儿开始表现出近似于日夜分明的睡觉模式。

value.def: If something approximates to something else, it is similar to it but is not exactly the same.
